A Grade 10 girl from Brindhaven in Verulam attempted to
commit suicide, by drinking brake fluid and cutting her wrist with a shaving
blade. According to Reaction Unit South Africa spokesperson Prem
Balram they were called out to the home by the child’s parents. When they arrived she had allegedly locked herself in the
bathroom. “Reaction officers arrived on scene and found the girl in an
emotional state. An open bottle of brake fluid was found next to her.
Paramedics treated her and transported her to Osindisweni Government Hospital. The parents say the child was found walking with her
boyfriend near a local garage the previous day during school hours. The altercation reportedly made her to attempt suicide by
slitting her wrists first. 